When I was 17 years old, I was in my room, praying, reading the Bible, and asking God, "What is it that He wants me to do?"

I was reading Mark 4:26, where it says, "And He said, 'So is the kingdom of God, as if a man should cast seed into the ground, and should sleep and rise night and day, and the seed should spring and grow; he knoweth not how. For the earth bringeth forth fruit of herself first the blade, then the ear, and then the full corn in the ear. But when the fruit is brought forth, immediately he putteth in the sickle, because the harvest is come.'"

He said, "Whereunto shall we liken the kingdom of God, or with what comparison shall we compare it? It is like a grain of mustard seed, which, when it is sown in the earth, is less than all the seeds that be in the earth, but when it is sown, it groweth up and becometh greater than all the herbs, and shooteth out great branches so that the fowls of the air may nest under its shadow."

Then I heard the Lord tell me, "So will be your company." From that moment, I knew that I am called to be a businessman and to have a company. I always wondered, all these years, now I am 42 years old, so 25 years ago. I was wondering all these years, "What does it mean that my business will be as a seed, as a grain of mustard seed that I will sow and it will grow sort of on its own? I will not know how, and it will become greater than all the other seeds and companies, and it will be a fortress to other people, a place of protection."

Just recently, maybe a couple of months back, or let me rephrase that, about five years ago, I started working with AI. It was back then when there was no ChatGPT; it was just tab completion using GitHub Copilot or Tab9. Ever since then, I was a very heavy user of AI. I started very early with all the major tools that came out, whether it be ChatGPT, GitHub Copilot, Claude code, etc. I was always the early adopter. 

And just recently, maybe only a couple of months ago, I began to realize that all that AI is, in the end, really just the sand that is taken from the ground. The processors that are responsible for all the inference that happens are made out of silicon, and of course all the other materials that we need for memory, etc., all come from the ground.

When later on people started experimenting with loops like /loop in Claude code or /goal in Codex, I also started experimenting with them and could see, for the first time in my life using AI, that these tools are capable of running for multiple hours, sometimes even days. The longest task that I had running so far was, I think, 19 hours.

Fast forward to this last Sunday, the 21st of June 2026. I was in the church, walking in the hallway, and I all of a sudden realized that the prophecy that God gave me, that my company will be like a mustard seed 

That if you think of an AI, the large language model that we use for coding, like GPT 5.5 or Opus 4.8, if you think that that is the ground, then the prompt, the task that we give to these loops, is the seed. When that process starts, it could be described in a similar way to what Mark 4:27-28 and further talks about: you cast a seed on the ground, you give a large language model a task, and then it works on it autonomously for multiple hours, even days. You yourself, as a developer or farmer, in the case of the scripture, don't know how it is growing. Day and night it grows, and you don't even know how.

Then this morning, June 23rd, 2026, I was walking outside, as I do every morning, praying and seeking God. I all of a sudden realized that in the natural world, all the information about what the seed should become is in the seed. The genetic information in the DNA is in the seed, and it provides a set of instructions on what the seed is supposed to become. It has direction, and it has the plan of what should be achieved. The earth on its own doesn't have the plan, but it has the capability. In the case of large language models, it has all the world's knowledge for all of human history, and it knows how to build the plan.

 So really, where the creative part happens, where the majority of human striving should be focused on, is building the seed, building the plan. What I would like to build in this project is such a system where the user can start working on the plan. It can cast their vision, and it can write down or dictate what it is that they want to achieve. They could then iterate back and forth together with AI on refining that vision, adding more clarity to it, coming up with use cases, user stories, specifications, all of that, really doing a thorough job on building the plan.

The user could then send this plan to a large language model via different harnesses like Codex, like Claude Code, like Pi coding agent, like Cursor, etc. The AI would then build the plan, but it wouldn't just build it as a black box where you maybe see a little bit of output of what's going on. There will be a really clear visual representation of what the plan is, what the plan was, what the seed was, and what the different steps that were specified in the seed were. Users will be able to see, as the AI works hour by hour, minute by minute, day by day, how the plan is coming to life. Let's say the user would come back in an hour or two and it would see that the AI has progressed through different milestones, etc.

As in our scripture from Mark 4, what that scripture doesn't talk about, but it's also very important, is the Farmer. There is a seed, there is a ground, but there are other elements that are needed that the scripture doesn't talk about. One of them is the Farmer. The Farmer is not the one that is causing the seed to grow. The Farmer is the one that is watching the whole process and maybe every now and then makes an executive decision that maybe he cuts off some leaves that don't belong to the plant or adds water, but overall he's not the one making the seed grow.

With our system, the user also needs to be able to make executive decisions as the plan is progressing. Also, the ground, in our case the model, the engine, should have the ability to ask users some questions or maybe surface some areas that it feels like we would like to have an input from the user, aka the Farmer. 


I imagine this to be a cross paltform desktop application